<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline">IMPORTANT</span> - Save your username and password, they may not be recoverable right now.</h4>

<h4><span style="text-decoration: underline">IMPORTANT</span> - Save this URL of this page so you can return to this page and upload more screenshots of your finished tutorials because there is no link to it right now.

<br><a href="https://railsgirls-signup.herokuapp.com/users/<%= @user.id %>/tutorials/<%= @tutorial.user_id %>"><strong>https://railsgirls-signup.herokuapp.com/users/<%= @user.id %>/tutorials/<%= @tutorial.user_id %></strong></a></h4>

<h4>- You will first also have to be signed in to upload tutorials. :)</h4>
<h4>- If it says your name here, <b><%= @user.first_name.capitalize %>,</b> you are signed in and your user id is: <%= @user.id %>.</h4>
<h4>- If you make a text file of a tutorial, take a screenshot of that and upload the screenshot.</h4>
<h4>- Be sure to refresh and/or restart the site from time to time because like I mentioned the site is a work in progress and I am making updates to it daily. :)</h4>
<hr/>
<h2>Second Level</h2>
<p>These 4 tutorials will help you get the most out of the Rails Girls workshop and determine your acceptance.
</p>

<p>Upload them as you complete them.<br/>
Don't wait until they are all done.<br/>
Once they are completed you will
be contacted about your acceptance status.
</p>
<p>
Do the best you can. Have fun learning.<br/>
Even if you think you know this stuff,
you will learn something new.
</p>

<p>
If you have any questions or this seems like too much work or too hard
let us know. railsgirlsla@gmail.com
</p>

<p>
If this feels too basic for you then you should
consider coaching at Rails Girls.
